{{Infobox user <!-- INFOBOX FORMATTING --------> | color = | fontcolor = | tablecolor = <!-- LEAD INFORMATION ----------> | status = | image =Ian_Maxwell_in_New_Orleans_2007.jpg | image_caption = Me in New Orleans, 2007 | image_width = 240px | name = Ian Maxwell | birthname = | gender = | birthdate = 1983 July 28 | birthplace = Boston, Massachusetts, USA | location = Dover, New Hampshire, USA <!-- FAMILY --> | marital status = Married | spouse = Jennifer (née Follis) | children = | siblings = | pets = <!-- EDUCATION & EMPLOYMENT ----> | occupation = | employer = | education = | college = | university = | highschool = <!-- INTERESTS & BELIEFS -------> | hobbies = | religion = | politics = | aliases = | movies = | books = | interests = <!-- CONTACT INFO --------------> | website = | blog = | email = | facebook = <!-- USERBOXES -----------------> | userboxes = {{user language|en|N}} {{user language|eo|3}} {{user language|fr|1}} {{user mathematics}} {{user ninja}} }}
I'm a graduate student in pure mathematics at the University of New Hampshire. My interests are a bit too diverse for my own good, but seem to be settling down; my ''major'' interests include foundations (particularly approached through categorical model theory) and algebraic topology. I like to do things categorically when I can get away with it.
My interest here is mostly in hacking on the math books, and getting them to the point where I can in good conscience suggest them in place of traditional textbooks for the courses I teach.

